      "message": "Just as a note (no need to do this right now) it may be simpler to name this Make and make the constructor private. Note that MakeHarfBuzz works something like that, but returns a std::unique_ptr so that failure is signaled by nullptr. In this case you really want std::optional so you can just return a value. The nice thing about doing this is that the class won\u0027t allow a non-fully-initialized instance to be floating about. (Of course this is an awkwardness of not being able to throw exceptions from the constructors.)",
